Instruction: With the battery removed from the power supply module, use an ohmmeter across the two PSU output cables (that feed Control Module 1 and ultimately the load) while all modules remain interconnected. Measure the resistance between the + and − rails. Then, systematically disconnect the chain at midpoints (e.g., unplug after control module 4, then after module 2 or 6, etc.) and re‑measure at the PSU side each time to localize where a low resistance or short between the rails appears.
