Instruction: With the PSU still connected to the rest of the system, insert the known‑good 12 V battery and measure the voltage directly across its terminals while it is installed (under load). Then remove the battery from the cube and again measure its open‑circuit voltage. Compare the loaded vs open‑circuit readings to determine whether the replacement battery collapses under load, indicating another defective battery despite correct wiring.
