DESCRIPTION: With the good battery inserted and all modules still connected, measure DC voltage at multiple points along the positive rail inside the PSU, if accessible via test pads or by slightly backing out the PSU output connector: (1) directly on the battery + terminal, (2) on the PCB trace or wiring immediately after the battery clip, (3) at any series protection element (fuse, switch, PTC) on both its input and output sides, and (4) at the internal solder joint feeding the external + output cable. Look for the exact point where voltage drops from 12 V to ~0.012 V to identify a high‑resistance/partial open connection.,
RESULT: Battery terminals measure 12.0 V to 0.0 V, but voltage on the battery internal resistor drops to 0.012 V on the positive side and 12.0 V on the negative side. POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED: Battery Internal Resistor terminal labeled (+) is at 0.012 V while its (−) terminal is at 12.0 V. All downstream PSU positive‑rail points (green LED resistor, green LED anode, PSU Output Cable (+)) measure ~0.012 V, indicating the low voltage persists along the positive rail beyond that resistor.
